" src="images/nav-updates.jpg" alt="Sign Up for Updates" name="nav_updates" width="214" height="37" border="0" /></a></div>            </div>            <div id="mainbkgrd">					<div id="homecolumn">						<div align="left">							<p class="homecopy">A gripping story of a child’s journey through hell and back.</p>							<p class="homecopy">There may be as many as 300,000 child soldiers, hopped-up on drugs and wielding AK-47s, in more than fifty conflicts around the world. Ishmael Beah used to be one of them.  He is one of the first to tell his story in his own words.</p>							<p class="homecopy">In A LONG WAY GONE, Beah, now twenty-six years old, tells a riveting story. At the age of twelve, he fled attacking rebels and wandered a land rendered unrecognizable by violence. By thirteen, he’d been picked up by the government army, and Beah, at heart a gentle boy, found that he was capable of truly terrible acts. Eventually released by the army and sent to a UNICEF rehabilitation center, he struggled to regain his humanity and to reenter the world of civilians, who viewed him with fear and suspicion. This is, at last, a story of redemption and hope.<br />							</p>						</div>						<p align="center"><a onmouseover="changeImages('starbucks_ent_home','images/starbucks_ent-over.gif');return true" onmouseout="changeImages('starbucks_ent_home','images/starbucks_ent.gif');return true" href="http://www.starbucks.com/entertainment" target="_blank"><img id="starbucks_ent_home" src="images/starbucks_ent.gif" alt="Starbuck's Featured Book" name="starbucks_ent_home" width="115" height="90" border="0" /></a></p>					</div>				</div>            <div id="footer">					<div align="center">                  <p class="bottomnav">Sarah Crichton Books / Farrar, Straus and Giroux | February 15, 2007 | <a class="bottomnav" href="http://www.fsgbooks.com" target="_blank">www.fsgbooks.com</a> | <a class="bottomnav" href="terms.html">Terms of Use</a> | <a class="bottomnav" href="p